    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.00/1408</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Panaman Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alfaro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation<note n="10" xml:id="d518fn10">Supplied by
                            the editor.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1927</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 373–D</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Pursuant to instructions from my
                    Government, I beg Your Excellency kindly to inform me whether the policy
                    outlined by Secretary of State Elihu Root in his notes of December 4, 1905,<note
                        n="11" xml:id="d518fn11">
                        <ref target="frus1905#pg_719">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1905, p. 719</ref>.</note>
                    arid February 21, 1906,<note n="12" xml:id="d518fn12">
                        <ref target="frus1906p2#pg_1203">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, 1906, pt. 2, p. 1203</ref>.</note> and by
                    Secretary of War William H. Taft in his instructions to the Governor of the
                    Canal Zone, Mr. Magoon, on April 26, 1906,<note n="13" xml:id="d518fn13">
                        <ref target="frus1906p2#pg_1206">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 1206</ref>.</note> continues to be the
                    policy of the Government of Your Excellency in connection with the question of
                    intervention by the United States in the internal affairs of the Republic of
                    Panama.</p>
                <p>My Government is especially interested in obtaining from the Government of Your
                    Excellency an express statement on this point at the present moment.</p>
                <p>With the expression [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. J. Alfaro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
